import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Set random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(42)

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for Pepsi and CocaCola from Jan 1, 2023 to Dec 31, 2023
start_date = "2023-01-01"
end_date = "2023-12-31"

print("Fetching data for Pepsi...")
pep_data = yf.download("PEP", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for CocaCola...")
ko_data = yf.download("KO", start=start_date, end=end_date)

# Extract the 'Close' column correctly from MultiIndex
pep_prices = pep_data['Close'].dropna()
ko_prices = ko_data['Close'].dropna()
print("Pepsi Prices Head:\n", pep_prices.head())
print("CocaCola Prices Head:\n", ko_prices.head())

# Step 2: Simulate a Random Walk
def random_walk_simulation(initial_price, steps, scale=1):
    random_steps = np.random.normal(loc=0, scale=scale, size=steps)
    random_steps[0] = initial_price  # Start at initial price
    return np.cumsum(random_steps)

pep_rw = random_walk_simulation(pep_prices.iloc[0], len(pep_prices), scale=5)
ko_rw = random_walk_simulation(ko_prices.iloc[0], len(ko_prices), scale=5)

# Step 3: Unit Root Test (ADF)
def unit_root_test(series, name):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f"\nUnit Root Test (ADF) for {name}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] > 0.05:
        print(f"{name} likely has a unit root (non-stationary).")
    else:
        print(f"{name} does not have a unit root (stationary).")

pep_returns = pep_prices.pct_change().dropna()
ko_returns = ko_prices.pct_change().dropna()

unit_root_test(pep_prices, "Pepsi Prices")
unit_root_test(ko_prices, "CocaCola Prices")
unit_root_test(pep_returns, "Pepsi Returns")
unit_root_test(ko_returns, "CocaCola Returns")

# Step 4: Fit ARMA Model (ARMA(1,1))
def fit_arma(series, name):
    model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 0, 1))
    fit = model.fit()
    print(f"\nARMA(1,1) Model Summary for {name}:")
    print(fit.summary().tables[1])
    return fit

pep_arma = fit_arma(pep_returns, "Pepsi Returns")
ko_arma = fit_arma(ko_returns, "CocaCola Returns")

# Step 5: Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))

# Random Walk vs Actual Prices
plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
plt.plot(pep_prices.index, pep_prices, label="Pepsi Actual", color="blue")
plt.plot(pep_prices.index, pep_rw, label="Pepsi Random Walk", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(ko_prices.index, ko_prices, label="CocaCola Actual", color="green")
plt.plot(ko_prices.index, ko_rw, label="CocaCola Random Walk", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("Stock Prices vs Random Walk Simulation")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price")
plt.legend()

# Returns
plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
plt.plot(pep_returns.index, pep_returns, label="Pepsi Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(ko_returns.index, ko_returns, label="CocaCola Returns", color="green")
plt.title("Daily Returns")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

# ARMA Forecasts (last 30 days)
pep_forecast = pep_arma.forecast(steps=30)
ko_forecast = ko_arma.forecast(steps=30)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=pep_returns.index[-1], periods=30, freq="B")

plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)
plt.plot(pep_returns.index[-30:], pep_returns[-30:], label="Pepsi Actual Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_index, pep_forecast, label="Pepsi ARMA Forecast", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(ko_returns.index[-30:], ko_returns[-30:], label="CocaCola Actual Returns", color="green")
plt.plot(forecast_index, ko_forecast, label="CocaCola ARMA Forecast", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("ARMA(1,1) Forecast vs Actual Returns (Last 30 Days)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Install required libraries in Colab
!pip install yfinance statsmodels matplotlib pandas numpy

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, coint
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Set random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(42)

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for Pepsi and CocaCola from Jan 1, 2023 to Dec 31, 2023
start_date = "2023-01-01"
end_date = "2023-12-31"

print("Fetching data for Pepsi...")
pep_data = yf.download("PEP", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for CocaCola...")
ko_data = yf.download("KO", start=start_date, end=end_date)

# Extract 'Close' prices correctly
pep_prices = pep_data['Close'].dropna()
ko_prices = ko_data['Close'].dropna()

# Align indices for cointegration test
combined = pd.concat([pep_prices, ko_prices], axis=1).dropna()
pep_prices = combined.iloc[:, 0]
ko_prices = combined.iloc[:, 1]

# Step 2: Simulate a Random Walk
def random_walk_simulation(initial_price, steps, scale=1):
    random_steps = np.random.normal(loc=0, scale=scale, size=steps)
    random_steps[0] = initial_price  # Start at initial price
    return np.cumsum(random_steps)

pep_rw = random_walk_simulation(pep_prices.iloc[0], len(pep_prices), scale=5)
ko_rw = random_walk_simulation(ko_prices.iloc[0], len(ko_prices), scale=5)

# Step 3: Unit Root Test (ADF)
def unit_root_test(series, name):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f"\nUnit Root Test (ADF) for {name}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] > 0.05:
        print(f"{name} likely has a unit root (non-stationary).")
    else:
        print(f"{name} does not have a unit root (stationary).")

pep_returns = pep_prices.pct_change().dropna()
ko_returns = ko_prices.pct_change().dropna()

unit_root_test(pep_prices, "Pepsi Prices")
unit_root_test(ko_prices, "CocaCola Prices")
unit_root_test(pep_returns, "Pepsi Returns")
unit_root_test(ko_returns, "CocaCola Returns")

# Step 4: Fit ARMA Model (ARMA(1,1))
def fit_arma(series, name):
    model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 0, 1))
    fit = model.fit()
    print(f"\nARMA(1,1) Model Summary for {name}:")
    print(fit.summary().tables[1])
    return fit

pep_arma = fit_arma(pep_returns, "Pepsi Returns")
ko_arma = fit_arma(ko_returns, "CocaCola Returns")

# Step 5: Correlogram and Partial Correlogram of Residuals
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)
plot_acf(pep_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of Pepsi ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 2)
plot_pacf(pep_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of Pepsi ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 3)
plot_acf(ko_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of CocaCola ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 4)
plot_pacf(ko_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of CocaCola ARMA Residuals")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Step 6: Cointegration Test (Engle-Granger)
print("\nCointegration Test (Engle-Granger) between Pepsi and CocaCola Prices:")
coint_result = coint(pep_prices, ko_prices)
print(f"Cointegration Test Statistic: {coint_result[0]:.4f}")
print(f"p-value: {coint_result[1]:.4f}")
print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in zip(['1%', '5%', '10%'], coint_result[2])})
if coint_result[1] < 0.05:
    print("Result: Reject the null hypothesis - Pepsi and CocaCola prices are cointegrated.")
else:
    print("Result: Fail to reject the null hypothesis - Pepsi and CocaCola prices are not cointegrated.")

# Step 7: Plotting Original Analyses
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))

# Random Walk vs Actual Prices
plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
plt.plot(pep_prices.index, pep_prices, label="Pepsi Actual", color="blue")
plt.plot(pep_prices.index, pep_rw, label="Pepsi Random Walk", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(ko_prices.index, ko_prices, label="CocaCola Actual", color="green")
plt.plot(ko_prices.index, ko_rw, label="CocaCola Random Walk", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("Stock Prices vs Random Walk Simulation")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price")
plt.legend()

# Returns
plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
plt.plot(pep_returns.index, pep_returns, label="Pepsi Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(ko_returns.index, ko_returns, label="CocaCola Returns", color="green")
plt.title("Daily Returns")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

# ARMA Forecasts (last 30 days)
pep_forecast = pep_arma.forecast(steps=30)
ko_forecast = ko_arma.forecast(steps=30)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=pep_returns.index[-1], periods=30, freq="B")

plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)
plt.plot(pep_returns.index[-30:], pep_returns[-30:], label="Pepsi Actual Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_index, pep_forecast, label="Pepsi ARMA Forecast", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(ko_returns.index[-30:], ko_returns[-30:], label="CocaCola Actual Returns", color="green")
plt.plot(forecast_index, ko_forecast, label="CocaCola ARMA Forecast", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("ARMA(1,1) Forecast vs Actual Returns (Last 30 Days)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Install required libraries in Colab
!pip install yfinance statsmodels matplotlib pandas numpy

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, coint
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Set random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(42)

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for Pepsi and CocaCola from Jan 1, 2023 to Dec 31, 2023
start_date = "2023-01-01"
end_date = "2023-12-31"

print("Fetching data for Pepsi...")
pep_data = yf.download("PEP", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for CocaCola...")
ko_data = yf.download("KO", start=start_date, end=end_date)

# Extract 'Close' prices correctly
pep_prices = pep_data['Close'].dropna()
ko_prices = ko_data['Close'].dropna()

# Align indices for cointegration test
combined = pd.concat([pep_prices, ko_prices], axis=1).dropna()
pep_prices = combined.iloc[:, 0]
ko_prices = combined.iloc[:, 1]

# Step 2: Simulate a Random Walk
def random_walk_simulation(initial_price, steps, scale=1):
    random_steps = np.random.normal(loc=0, scale=scale, size=steps)
    random_steps[0] = initial_price  # Start at initial price
    return np.cumsum(random_steps)

pep_rw = random_walk_simulation(pep_prices.iloc[0], len(pep_prices), scale=5)
ko_rw = random_walk_simulation(ko_prices.iloc[0], len(ko_prices), scale=5)

# Step 3: Unit Root Test (ADF)
def unit_root_test(series, name):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f"\nUnit Root Test (ADF) for {name}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] > 0.05:
        print(f"{name} likely has a unit root (non-stationary).")
    else:
        print(f"{name} does not have a unit root (stationary).")

pep_returns = pep_prices.pct_change().dropna()
ko_returns = ko_prices.pct_change().dropna()

unit_root_test(pep_prices, "Pepsi Prices")
unit_root_test(ko_prices, "CocaCola Prices")
unit_root_test(pep_returns, "Pepsi Returns")
unit_root_test(ko_returns, "CocaCola Returns")

# Step 4: Fit ARMA Model (ARMA(1,1))
def fit_arma(series, name):
    model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 0, 1))
    fit = model.fit()
    print(f"\nARMA(1,1) Model Summary for {name}:")
    print(fit.summary().tables[1])
    return fit

pep_arma = fit_arma(pep_returns, "Pepsi Returns")
ko_arma = fit_arma(ko_returns, "CocaCola Returns")

# Step 5: Correlogram and Partial Correlogram of Residuals
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)
plot_acf(pep_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of Pepsi ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 2)
plot_pacf(pep_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of Pepsi ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 3)
plot_acf(ko_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of CocaCola ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 4)
plot_pacf(ko_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of CocaCola ARMA Residuals")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Step 6: Cointegration Test (Engle-Granger)
print("\nCointegration Test (Engle-Granger) between Pepsi and CocaCola Prices:")
coint_result = coint(pep_prices, ko_prices)
print(f"Cointegration Test Statistic: {coint_result[0]:.4f}")
print(f"p-value: {coint_result[1]:.4f}")
print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in zip(['1%', '5%', '10%'], coint_result[2])})
if coint_result[1] < 0.05:
    print("Result: Reject the null hypothesis - Pepsi and CocaCola prices are cointegrated.")
else:
    print("Result: Fail to reject the null hypothesis - Pepsi and CocaCola prices are not cointegrated.")

# Step 7: Plotting Original Analyses
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))

# Random Walk vs Actual Prices
plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
plt.plot(pep_prices.index, pep_prices, label="Pepsi Actual", color="blue")
plt.plot(pep_prices.index, pep_rw, label="Pepsi Random Walk", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(ko_prices.index, ko_prices, label="CocaCola Actual", color="green")
plt.plot(ko_prices.index, ko_rw, label="CocaCola Random Walk", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("Stock Prices vs Random Walk Simulation")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price")
plt.legend()

# Returns
plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
plt.plot(pep_returns.index, pep_returns, label="Pepsi Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(ko_returns.index, ko_returns, label="CocaCola Returns", color="green")
plt.title("Daily Returns")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

# ARMA Forecasts (last 30 days)
pep_forecast = pep_arma.forecast(steps=30)
ko_forecast = ko_arma.forecast(steps=30)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=pep_returns.index[-1], periods=30, freq="B")

plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)
plt.plot(pep_returns.index[-30:], pep_returns[-30:], label="Pepsi Actual Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_index, pep_forecast, label="Pepsi ARMA Forecast", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(ko_returns.index[-30:], ko_returns[-30:], label="CocaCola Actual Returns", color="green")
plt.plot(forecast_index, ko_forecast, label="CocaCola ARMA Forecast", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("ARMA(1,1) Forecast vs Actual Returns (Last 30 Days)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Install required libraries in Colab
!pip install yfinance statsmodels matplotlib pandas numpy

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, coint
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Set random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(42)

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for Intel and AMD from Mar 1, 2023 to Oct 31, 2023
start_date = "2023-03-01"
end_date = "2023-10-31"

print("Fetching data for Intel...")
intc_data = yf.download("INTC", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for AMD...")
amd_data = yf.download("AMD", start=start_date, end=end_date)

# Extract 'Close' prices correctly
intc_prices = intc_data['Close'].dropna()
amd_prices = amd_data['Close'].dropna()
print("Intel Prices Head:\n", intc_prices.head())
print("AMD Prices Head:\n", amd_prices.head())

# Align indices for cointegration test
combined = pd.concat([intc_prices, amd_prices], axis=1).dropna()
intc_prices = combined.iloc[:, 0]
amd_prices = combined.iloc[:, 1]

# Step 2: Simulate a Random Walk
def random_walk_simulation(initial_price, steps, scale=1):
    random_steps = np.random.normal(loc=0, scale=scale, size=steps)
    random_steps[0] = initial_price  # Start at initial price
    return np.cumsum(random_steps)

intc_rw = random_walk_simulation(intc_prices.iloc[0], len(intc_prices), scale=5)
amd_rw = random_walk_simulation(amd_prices.iloc[0], len(amd_prices), scale=5)

# Step 3: Unit Root Test (ADF)
def unit_root_test(series, name):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f"\nUnit Root Test (ADF) for {name}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] > 0.05:
        print(f"{name} likely has a unit root (non-stationary).")
    else:
        print(f"{name} does not have a unit root (stationary).")

intc_returns = intc_prices.pct_change().dropna()
amd_returns = amd_prices.pct_change().dropna()

unit_root_test(intc_prices, "Intel Prices")
unit_root_test(amd_prices, "AMD Prices")
unit_root_test(intc_returns, "Intel Returns")
unit_root_test(amd_returns, "AMD Returns")

# Step 4: Fit ARMA Model (ARMA(1,1))
def fit_arma(series, name):
    model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 0, 1))
    fit = model.fit()
    print(f"\nARMA(1,1) Model Summary for {name}:")
    print(fit.summary().tables[1])
    return fit

intc_arma = fit_arma(intc_returns, "Intel Returns")
amd_arma = fit_arma(amd_returns, "AMD Returns")

# Step 5: Correlogram and Partial Correlogram of Residuals
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)
plot_acf(intc_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of Intel ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 2)
plot_pacf(intc_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of Intel ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 3)
plot_acf(amd_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of AMD ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 4)
plot_pacf(amd_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of AMD ARMA Residuals")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Step 6: Cointegration Test (Engle-Granger)
print("\nCointegration Test (Engle-Granger) between Intel and AMD Prices:")
coint_result = coint(intc_prices, amd_prices)
print(f"Cointegration Test Statistic: {coint_result[0]:.4f}")
print(f"p-value: {coint_result[1]:.4f}")
print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in zip(['1%', '5%', '10%'], coint_result[2])})
if coint_result[1] < 0.05:
    print("Result: Reject the null hypothesis - Intel and AMD prices are cointegrated.")
else:
    print("Result: Fail to reject the null hypothesis - Intel and AMD prices are not cointegrated.")

# Step 7: Plotting Original Analyses
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))

# Random Walk vs Actual Prices
plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
plt.plot(intc_prices.index, intc_prices, label="Intel Actual", color="blue")
plt.plot(intc_prices.index, intc_rw, label="Intel Random Walk", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(amd_prices.index, amd_prices, label="AMD Actual", color="green")
plt.plot(amd_prices.index, amd_rw, label="AMD Random Walk", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("Stock Prices vs Random Walk Simulation")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price")
plt.legend()

# Returns
plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
plt.plot(intc_returns.index, intc_returns, label="Intel Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(amd_returns.index, amd_returns, label="AMD Returns", color="green")
plt.title("Daily Returns")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

# ARMA Forecasts (last 30 days)
intc_forecast = intc_arma.forecast(steps=30)
amd_forecast = amd_arma.forecast(steps=30)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=intc_returns.index[-1], periods=30, freq="B")

plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)
plt.plot(intc_returns.index[-30:], intc_returns[-30:], label="Intel Actual Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_index, intc_forecast, label="Intel ARMA Forecast", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(amd_returns.index[-30:], amd_returns[-30:], label="AMD Actual Returns", color="green")
plt.plot(forecast_index, amd_forecast, label="AMD ARMA Forecast", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("ARMA(1,1) Forecast vs Actual Returns (Last 30 Days)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
